f war. Ranging across the globe, Galeotti shows how today’s conflicts are fought with everything from disinformation and espionage to crime and subversion, leading to instability within countries and a legitimacy crisis across the globe. But rather than suggest that we hope for a return to a bygone era of “stable” warfare, Galeotti details ways of surviving, adapting, and taking advantage of the opportunities presented by this new reality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aMilitary art and science. 0aWorld politics. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300265132zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300265132423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300265132/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles